{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0187BjftJgtNfmrT1qYbYHcr","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01JuZd6523jkYmVRp93X3Ld1","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n spark-pi create configmap config-audit --from-literal=findings.txt=\"$(cat <<'FINDINGS'\n====================================================================\nSPARK-PI NAMESPACE — COMPLIANCE AUDIT REPORT\nAudit date : 2026-06-26\nAuditor    : automated read-only inspection\nScope      : RBAC, resource limits, image provenance, security contexts,\n             network policies, namespace-level controls\n====================================================================\n\n--- SECTION 1: PASSING CONTROLS ---\n\n[PASS] Dedicated ServiceAccount\n  A dedicated ServiceAccount 'spark-pi' exists in the namespace.\n  All three workloads (spark-master Deployment, spark-worker Deployment,\n  spark-pi Job) explicitly reference serviceAccountName: spark-pi, so they\n  do NOT run under the 'default' account.\n\n[PASS] RBAC Role scoped to namespace\n  Role 'spark-pi-role' is a namespaced Role (not a ClusterRole).\n  It is limited to core-API resources: pods, services, configmaps,\n  persistentvolumeclaims. No cluster-wide resources are granted.\n\n[PASS] RoleBinding correctly wired\n  RoleBinding 'spark-pi-role-binding' binds 'spark-pi-role' to the\n  'spark-pi' ServiceAccount. No wildcards or extra subjects present.\n\n[PASS] Resource limits set on all containers\n  Every container (spark-master, spark-worker, spark-submit job) defines\n  both requests and limits:\n    cpu    requests=200m   limits=500m\n    memory requests=512Mi  limits=1Gi\n  This prevents unbounded CPU/memory consumption.\n\n[PASS] Pinned image tag (non-latest)\n  All containers use apache/spark:3.5.3. The 'latest' tag is not used,\n  reducing the risk of unintended version drift.\n\n[PASS] Job restart policy\n  The spark-pi Job sets restartPolicy=Never and backoffLimit=0, preventing\n  uncontrolled retry loops on failure.\n\n--- SECTION 2: GAPS / FINDINGS ---\n\n[GAP-1] No pod or container securityContext on any workload  (HIGH)\n  All three workloads (spark-master, spark-worker, spark-pi job) have\n  securityContext: {} at both the pod level and the container level.\n  Missing hardening fields:\n    - runAsNonRoot: true          (containers may run as UID 0 / root)\n    - runAsUser / runAsGroup      (no explicit UID/GID enforced)\n    - allowPrivilegeEscalation: false  (not disabled)\n    - readOnlyRootFilesystem: true     (not set)\n    - capabilities.drop: [ALL]        (no capability reduction)\n  Recommendation: add a securityContext to each container at minimum with\n  allowPrivilegeEscalation: false and capabilities.drop: [ALL]; set\n  runAsNonRoot: true and a non-zero runAsUser.\n\n[GAP-2] Image not pinned by digest  (MEDIUM)\n  Image tag apache/spark:3.5.3 is a mutable tag. A compromised or\n  accidentally overwritten tag in Docker Hub would cause new pods to pull\n  a different image without any manifest change in the cluster.\n  Recommendation: pin images by SHA-256 digest, e.g.\n    apache/spark:3.5.3@sha256:<digest>\n  Also note: imagePullPolicy is IfNotPresent on all pods, so if the node\n  already has the image cached the change would not be noticed immediately.\n\n[GAP-3] No NetworkPolicy defined  (HIGH)\n  The namespace contains no NetworkPolicy resources. All pods can receive\n  and initiate traffic to any pod in the cluster and to external endpoints.\n  Recommendation: create a default-deny ingress+egress NetworkPolicy for\n  the namespace and then explicitly allow only required flows (e.g.,\n  worker → master on port 7077, master WebUI on 8080 from authorised\n  sources, DNS on 53/UDP).\n\n[GAP-4] RBAC Role grants overly broad write verbs on pods  (MEDIUM)\n  'spark-pi-role' grants create/get/list/watch/delete/update/patch on pods.\n  The verbs delete, update, patch on pods are permissive; a compromised\n  workload running under this account could delete or mutate other pods in\n  the namespace.\n  Additionally, persistentvolumeclaims is listed in the role but no PVCs\n  exist or are required by the current workloads, violating least-privilege.\n  Recommendation: restrict verbs to only those required (likely\n  create/get/list/watch for pods); remove persistentvolumeclaims if unused.\n\n[GAP-5] No namespace-level LimitRange or ResourceQuota  (LOW)\n  Individual containers have limits set, but there is no LimitRange (to\n  enforce defaults for any future container that omits limits) and no\n  ResourceQuota (to cap total namespace consumption).\n  Recommendation: add a ResourceQuota capping total CPU and memory for the\n  namespace, and a LimitRange providing default limits/requests for pods\n  that do not specify them.\n\n--- SECTION 3: SUMMARY ---\n\nControls evaluated : 10\nPassing            : 5\nGaps identified    : 5  (2 HIGH, 2 MEDIUM, 1 LOW)\n\nPriority remediation order:\n  1. Add securityContext to all workloads (GAP-1)\n  2. Enforce NetworkPolicy default-deny + allow-list (GAP-3)\n  3. Pin images by digest (GAP-2)\n  4. Tighten RBAC verbs; remove unused PVC rule (GAP-4)\n  5. Add LimitRange and ResourceQuota (GAP-5)\n\nNo changes were made to the cluster during this audit.\n====================================================================\nFINDINGS)\" 2>&1","description":"Create config-audit ConfigMap with audit findings"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1395,"cache_read_input_tokens":33543,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1395},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ecacabe8-c22b-41a6-a2fc-48c003317577","uuid":"a3d7a77b-7f01-4fae-9631-13ed635f9e5d","request_id":"req_011CcRK4iCDjDGPcK