{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_018DXqGByQCUbFew9bRqMAvs","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The ConfigMap `config-audit` is created and populated. Here's a summary of what the audit found:\n\n**5 Passing controls:**\n- Dedicated `spark-pi` ServiceAccount used by all workloads (not `default`)\n- RBAC Role is namespace-scoped (not a ClusterRole)\n- RoleBinding correctly wired to the dedicated SA\n- Resource requests+limits set on every container (cpu: 200m/500m, memory: 512Mi/1Gi)\n- Pinned image tag `apache/spark:3.5.3` (not `latest`)\n\n**5 Gaps identified:**\n1. **[HIGH]** No securityContext on any workload — containers may run as root, privilege escalation not disabled, no capability drop\n2. **[HIGH]** No NetworkPolicy — unrestricted pod-to-pod and egress traffic\n3. **[MEDIUM]** Image pinned by tag only, not by SHA-256 digest — mutable tag is a supply-chain risk\n4. **[MEDIUM]** RBAC role grants `delete`/`update`/`patch` on pods and lists `persistentvolumeclaims` which aren't used — violates least-privilege\n5. **[LOW]** No LimitRange or ResourceQuota at the namespace level\n\nNo changes were made to the live cluster during the audit."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":361,"cache_read_input_tokens":36668,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":361},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ecacabe8-c22b-41a6-a2fc-48c003317577","uuid":"f32aa04f-2acd-4508-af54-ce141d4613da","request_id":"req_011CcRK7NiXRngWS9tmFZ7Sv"}
